de.fhg.iml.packer.test
Class IMLPackerTest

java.lang.Object
  de.fhg.iml.packer.test.IMLPackerTest

public class IMLPackerTest
extends java.lang.Object

JUnit test of the packer implementation delivered by the IMLPackerFactory.

The requirements for the integral packer are defined by the interface IntegralPacker from the EfficientLoad packer API.

Author:
kschroeder

testBasicBehaviour1

public void testBasicBehaviour1()
Tests the following part of the contract:
  • The packer delivers either a legal loading plan that contains at least one package for each transport or no loading plan at all.
  • If the packer delivers no loading plan at all the input transports are unchanged.
Tests with volume limitation.

testBasicBehaviour2

public void testBasicBehaviour2()
Tests the following part of the contract:
  • The packer delivers either a legal loading plan that contains at least one package for each transport or no loading plan at all.
  • If the packer delivers no loading plan at all the input transports are unchanged.
Tests with weight limitation.

transportDivisionTest

public void transportDivisionTest()
Tests the following part of the contract:
  • The packer may pack only a fraction of the packages of a transport if the transport is marked as dividable. In this case the transport is divided and the remainder is returned with the loading result.
Tests with volume limitation.
